@title - Operations
# Creation - Spawning a Process
@def fork() - System Call that creates an exact copy of parent process in seperate memory space
* only difference between fork and parent process is process ID
@def exec() - System call that Replaces the text(code)/data with the new program and then executes
@def wait() - System call wait for some proecess (like the child you just spawned off) to terminate
@def exit() - System call that is hit when you reach the end of a program, lets the parent process know to deallocate resources. Terminates and returns to wait() in parent

